decision_details:
- the Government has allocated Rs. 1878 Million to the National Housing Development Authority for the modernization of Multi?storeyed Housing Schemes and provision of infrastructure facilities. It is expected to carry out renovation work of the following 12 housing schemes under the 3rd phase of “Nagamu Purawara”:

		*	Saunders Place Housing Scheme 		-	57 houses;
		*	Anderson Housing Scheme 		-        816 house;
		*	117 Watta - Elvitigala Housing  Scheme 
			for low income earners 			-	32 houses;
		*	Kandawalawatta Housing Scheme	-	72 houses;
		*	Mayura Place Housing Scheme - 
			Wellawatta					-	24 houses;
		*	Torrington New Housing Scheme -
			Phase IV					-	48 houses;
		*	797 Watta Housing Scheme (Phase II)	-        116 houses;
		*	Vipulasena Mawatha Housing Scheme,	-	52 houses 
			Shops and Office complex				and
									 	20 shops
		*	Restoring drain system, Mahawatta	-	20 houses;
		*	St Anthony's Housing Scheme - 
			Kollupitiya					-	64 houses;
		*	Mattegoda Housing Scheme		-      1122 houses; and
		*	Ranpokunagama Housing Scheme -
			Completing the remaining work of the 
			sewage treatment plant			-        322 houses
